<h1 class="hero-h">How much does an AI CMO cost? <em>2026 pricing breakdown.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Three categories of AI CMO solutions cost very different amounts. Here is the realistic 2026 range for each, who they fit, and how the AI CMO layer compares to the human fractional CMO layer.</p>
<div class="verdict"><div class="verdict-l">Short answer</div><p class="verdict-p">Standalone AI CMO products run roughly $200 to $2,000 per month. A DIY Claude or ChatGPT build costs $20 to $200 per month in subscriptions plus setup time. A fractional CMO costs $8,000 to $25,000 per month. Most B2B mid-market companies pair an AI execution layer with a human strategy layer.</p></div>
<p class="note">Pricing references are as of June 2026 and may change. Always confirm current pricing on the vendor site before committing.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">The pricing tiers</h2>
<p class="body">There are three meaningfully different things people mean by 'AI CMO':</p>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Standalone AI CMO products ($200 to $2,000 / month).</strong> Branded AI CMO platforms (Okara, Lindy CMO, similar). Pre-built marketing workflows, brand voice, content production. Pricing scales with seats and usage.</li>
<li><strong>DIY Claude or ChatGPT AI CMO ($20 to $200 / month).</strong> Claude Pro or Team, ChatGPT Plus or Team, plus Projects with marketing playbooks loaded. Requires a few weeks of setup but is by far the cheapest.</li>
<li><strong>Fractional CMO with AI tooling ($8,000 to $25,000 / month).</strong> A human strategy and leadership layer who also runs AI tooling under them. Different category; covers strategy and team management that no software product handles.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">What drives the number up or down</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Seats and usage.</strong> Standalone products scale per-seat and per-output.</li>
<li><strong>Brand-voice setup.</strong> Standalone products include this; DIY builds it once and stores it.</li>
<li><strong>Strategy ownership.</strong> AI CMO products execute; they do not own strategy. A fractional CMO does.</li>
<li><strong>Integration depth.</strong> CRM, CMS, and ad-platform integration costs more in standalone products; you build it yourself in DIY.</li>
<li><strong>Compliance posture.</strong> Standalone vendors have varying data-handling terms; DIY uses the underlying assistant's Team/Enterprise terms.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Where it fits the cost ladder</h2>
<table class="cmp-table">
<thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Typical cost</th><th>Best when</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>Standalone AI CMO product</td><td>$200 to $2,000 / month</td><td>Marketing teams that want pre-built workflows</td></tr>
<tr><td>DIY Claude or ChatGPT AI CMO</td><td>$20 to $200 / month</td><td>Teams comfortable building their own marketing prompt library</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fractional CMO</td><td>$8,000 to $25,000 / month</td><td>Companies that need strategy and leadership, not just execution</td></tr>
<tr><td>Full-time CMO</td><td>$300,000 to $500,000 / year all-in</td><td>Companies where marketing is the primary growth engine</td></tr>
<tr><td>Marketing agency</td><td>$5,000 to $30,000 / month</td><td>Channel execution against a clear plan</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Who should pay for it</h2>
<ul class="ul">
<li><strong>Use a standalone AI CMO product if</strong> you want pre-built marketing workflows and brand voice with low setup overhead.</li>
<li><strong>Use a DIY Claude or ChatGPT AI CMO if</strong> you have a marketer who will spend a few weeks building reusable Projects and prompts.</li>
<li><strong>Pair AI tooling with a fractional CMO if</strong> you need strategy and team leadership, not just execution.</li>
<li><strong>Do not use any AI CMO as a substitute for strategy</strong> until someone has set it. AI executes the wrong plan faster than humans do.</li>
</ul>
</div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner">
<h2 class="h2">Frequently asked questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can an AI CMO replace a fractional CMO?</div><div class="faq-a">No. AI CMO products replace execution work (campaign briefs, copy drafts, reporting summaries). Strategy, team leadership, and board accountability still require a human.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is DIY really cheaper than a standalone AI CMO product?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes, by an order of magnitude in raw subscription costs. The cost shows up in setup time and ongoing prompt management. Worth it for teams that want flexibility and lower lock-in.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How do I budget for an AI CMO in 2026?</div><div class="faq-a">Most B2B mid-market companies should budget $50 to $500 per month for the AI execution layer (DIY or low-tier standalone) and add a $10,000 to $20,000 per month fractional CMO for strategy.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are standalone AI CMO products worth the premium?</div><div class="faq-a">Sometimes. The premium pays for marketing-team-shaped workflows, brand voice management, and lower setup time. Teams without internal marketing-ops capacity often value that. Technical teams usually do not.</div></div>
<div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Will AI CMO costs come down?</div><div class="faq-a">Standalone product pricing is competitive and trending down in real terms as the category matures. Underlying frontier-model prices continue to drop too. Budget annually and re-evaluate.</div></div>
</div></section>

